expected behaviour\r\nwhen upgrading the server, it should not be be shown \"owncloud is in maintenance mode\"\r\n\r\n### actual behaviour\r\nthis is shown\r\n\r\n### steps to reproduce\r\n1. having the installed version owncloud 4.5.8, we upgrade to 5.0.6, following the steps on http://doc.owncloud.org/server/5.0/admin_manual/maintenance/update.html\r\n2. once everything is done, we open a chrome browser and access to our server\r\n3. it is shown the information that the server is being upgraded and it could take a bit\r\n4. since nothing else happens, we refresh the screen and it is shown, \"owncloud is in maintenance mode\"\r\n5. by looking at forum.owncloud.org, i notice that it can be solved by changing  config.php maintenance to true, it has worked\r\n\r\ni have done the same, upgrade from 4.5.8 to 5.0.6 and accessed to the server with firefox, and it has worked just fine at a first step.\r\n\r\n### server configuration\r\nopen suse 12.2\r\nsqlite3\r\n\r\n### client configuration\r\nbrowser: chrome\r\n\r\noperating system: mac 10.7.5\r\n\r\n### logs\r\n\r\n\r\n#### browser log\r\n```\r\nget http://10.40.40.2/owncloud/index.php/core/routes.json 503 (service temporarily unavailable)\r\n```\r\n","closed_by":{"login":"jancborchardt","id":925062,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/2fd3f4d5d762955e5b603794a888fa97?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f84ec51f9ceed468217d4e13abf78da9c.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"2fd3f4d5d762955e5b603794a888fa97","url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt","html_url":"https://github.com/jancborchardt","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.c